crowdsourced_yara_results.description: Detects CowTunnel Linux reverse-proxy tunnel (NSS wrapper + FRP client) used for outbound access/pivoting in React2Shell activity
crowdsourced_yara_results.author: RussianPanda

attributes.magic: ELF 64-bit LSB executable, x86-64, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, no section header

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The sample is a multi-functional backdoor based on the `frp` (Fast Reverse Proxy) tool. It establishes a reverse tunnel for command and control. Its primary malicious capabilities include providing remote shell access by implementing a telnet daemon that spawns `/bin/login`, and creating a new privileged user with `sudo useradd` and `usermod`. The malware also decrypts an embedded configuration using the hardcoded key "bigeelaminoacow" and performs system fingerprinting to identify the init system (e.g., systemd, upstart).
